Discover 5 recent security incidents

In this activity, I researched several recent cybersecurity incidents to understand real-world security failures and their impact.

1. Optus Data Breach 2022 (Australia)  
The Optus data breach exposed personal information of millions of customers due to an API vulnerability. This incident shows how poor access control can lead to large-scale data leaks.
https://www.qld.gov.au/community/your-home-community/cyber-security/cyber-security-for-queenslanders/case-studies/optus-data-breach

2. Medibank Data Breach 2022 
Medibank suffered a cyberattack where sensitive health data was stolen and leaked. This demonstrates the importance of securing sensitive information and protecting against unauthorized access.
https://www.qld.gov.au/community/your-home-community/cyber-security/cyber-security-for-queenslanders/case-studies/medibank-private-cyber-incident

3. MOVEit File Transfer Vulnerability 2023
A vulnerability in MOVEit software was exploited by attackers to access data from multiple organizations. This highlights the risks of software vulnerabilities and the need for regular updates and patching.
https://www.ncsc.gov.uk/information/moveit-vulnerability

4. MGM Resorts Cyberattack 2023
MGM Resorts experienced a cyberattack that disrupted hotel systems and services. This shows how cyberattacks can affect real-world operations and cause financial and reputational damage.
https://netwrix.com/en/resources/blog/mgm-cyber-attack/

5. Deepfake Scam Incidents  
There have been cases where attackers used AI-generated voices or videos to impersonate individuals and trick victims into transferring money. This demonstrates emerging threats from AI technologies in cybersecurity.
https://www.qld.gov.au/community/your-home-community/cyber-security/cyber-security-for-queenslanders/case-studies/deepfake-scams
